{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3661011,"name":"Yishai Levy","username":"levyishai","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/levyishai/{size}/264719_2.png","created_at":"2025-06-23T13:11:06.479Z","cooked":"<p>This is the general code I’m running:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">static const String apiKey = "APIKEY";
static final Dio dio = Dio(BaseOptions(
    headers: &lt;String, String&gt;{"X-TBA-Auth-Key": apiKey},
    baseUrl: "https://www.thebluealliance.com/api/v3",
));

static final TbaApiV3 tbaApi = TbaApiV3(dio: dio);
static final EventApi tbaEventApi = tbaApi.getEventApi();

static Future&lt;BuiltList&lt;Match&gt;?&gt; getCMPMatches() async {
  final Response&lt;BuiltList&lt;Match&gt;&gt; eventsResponse = await tbaEventApi.getEventMatches(eventKey: "2025cmptx");
  return eventsResponse.data;
}
</code></pre>
<p>I’m getting the following error:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">DartError: DioException [bad response]: This exception was thrown because the response has a status code of 404 and RequestOptions.validateStatus
was configured to throw for this status code.
The status code of 404 has the following meaning: "Client error - the request contains bad syntax or cannot be fulfilled"
</code></pre>
<p>I verified the dio itself is good, and that the event key is valid using this piece of code (which returned 200):</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">final resp = await dio.get&lt;List&lt;dynamic&gt;&gt;(
  '/event/2025cmptx/matches',
  options: Options(validateStatus: (_) =&gt; true),
);
print(resp.statusCode);
print((resp.data?.first) ?? 'No data');
</code></pre>
<p>Might this be an internal library problem? Has anyone used the <span class="abbreviation">TBA<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="The Blue Alliance, a site for FIRST Robotics Competition event data"></template></span> API in dart recently and can help here? Is the better way to go about this is just to do the requests manually without the api library?</p>
